        <h1>Getting Started</h1>
        <h3>Download SteamVR</h3>
        <p>First, <a href="steam://install/2508200">download and install SteamVR</a> using Steam.</p>

        <h3>Download Zephyr Overlay</h3>
        <p>Next, <a href="#">download Zephyr Overlay</a> using Steam.</p>

        <h3>Login to Zephyr Overlay</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Next, launch SteamVR and put on your VR headset. Pull up the VR Dashboard and find the Zephyr icon at the bottom of the dashboard.</li>
            <li>Select the Zephyr icon to load the Zephyr overlay. Select "Login" to begin the login process.</li>
            <li>Remove your VR headset and use the window on your desktop to login using your Steam account.</li>
            <li>Return to VR when prompted.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Download Zephyr for Android</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Next, <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.texasgamer.zephyr&hl=en">download Zephyr for Android</a> from the Google Play Store.</li>
            <li>Open Zephyr on your Android phone and login using your Steam account.</li>
            <li>Onced logged in, select "Connect" to begin mirroring notifications into VR.</li>
        </ul>

